1
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:13,720
[Year 2005, Luoche Village]

2
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:50,320
Uncle.

3
00:02:55,260 --> 00:02:58,760
[Sandstorm]
[Episode 6]

4
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:01,870
In the ninth year of Yonghe,
during the year of Guichou,

5
00:03:02,150 --> 00:03:03,680
in the early spring,

6
00:03:03,910 --> 00:03:07,120
we gathered at the Lan Pavilion
in Shanyin, Kuaiji County,

7
00:03:07,470 --> 00:03:08,960
for a purification ritual.

8
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:10,750
Many wise men attended...

9
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,910
Are you indicating Yingying and Dafu?

10
00:03:13,030 --> 00:03:14,120
Of course, I remember.

11
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:15,800
Back then,

12
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:18,150
I was in charge of Yingying's class.

13
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:21,520
As for Fu, he was in the
experimental class for our grade.

14
00:03:22,630 --> 00:03:24,470
These two kids came from poor families.

15
00:03:24,750 --> 00:03:27,240
They were two years older
than the other classmates.

16
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:30,280
They were the eldest in the class.

17
00:03:31,470 --> 00:03:32,590
Both of them

18
00:03:33,340 --> 00:03:34,820
had excellent grades.

19
00:03:35,710 --> 00:03:38,190
They obtained the highest scores in the
National College Entrance Examination.

20
00:03:38,870 --> 00:03:40,940
Do you remember
which colleges they attended?

21
00:03:41,990 --> 00:03:44,590
Fu should've attended
to the Provincial University.

22
00:03:44,940 --> 00:03:46,590
For Yingying, it's a pity.

23
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:50,340
Her exam score wasn't
any worse than her brother's.

24
00:03:50,710 --> 00:03:52,620
She should've attended
to the Provincial Medical University.

25
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:55,380
Her first choice was
the Provincial Medical University, too.

26
00:03:56,220 --> 00:03:57,430
But, unfortunately,

27
00:03:58,430 --> 00:04:01,470
she ended up attending to
a college in the provincial capital.

28
00:04:01,820 --> 00:04:03,750
Why a college instead
of the medical university?

29
00:04:04,710 --> 00:04:06,660
Their family couldn't afford
to send both to the university.

30
00:04:06,750 --> 00:04:08,190
They had to sacrifice Yingying.

31
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:12,030
That year, she was the student
with the highest score

32
00:04:12,030 --> 00:04:13,750
who was admitted to that college.

33
00:04:14,270 --> 00:04:15,950
The college was thrilled

34
00:04:17,180 --> 00:04:18,180
to have such an outstanding student,

35
00:04:18,590 --> 00:04:20,420
waiving all her tuition fee

36
00:04:20,540 --> 00:04:22,590
and giving her
a huge amount of scholarship.

37
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:26,150
The class is over.

38
00:04:26,150 --> 00:04:26,950
The class is over.

39
00:04:33,070 --> 00:04:33,950
What a shame!

40
00:04:34,420 --> 00:04:35,420
Everyone feels the same.

41
00:04:36,910 --> 00:04:38,740
I even had a special talk
with her back then.

42
00:04:44,340 --> 00:04:45,780
You shouldn't slack off in the college.

43
00:04:46,510 --> 00:04:47,590
Thank you, Teacher Guo.

44
00:04:47,830 --> 00:04:48,830
Goodbye, Teacher Guo.

45
00:04:48,980 --> 00:04:49,830
Alright, you may leave.

46
00:05:02,070 --> 00:05:02,980
Teacher Guo.

47
00:05:06,590 --> 00:05:08,780
Liu Yingying, have you
made up your mind?

48
00:05:08,910 --> 00:05:10,180
Do you really want
to change your option?

49
00:05:11,740 --> 00:05:13,220
You could have gone
to the Medical University.

50
00:05:13,340 --> 00:05:15,220
Why do you choose to attend a college?

51
00:05:16,380 --> 00:05:17,740
After graduating
from the Medical University,

52
00:05:17,860 --> 00:05:19,390
you could attend the
postgraduate entrance examination,

53
00:05:19,540 --> 00:05:22,070
or directly work at a hospital.

54
00:05:22,130 --> 00:05:24,320
You could become a doctor
after a few years of internship.

55
00:05:24,330 --> 00:05:25,340
Isn't that good?

56
00:05:28,420 --> 00:05:30,590
I've made up my mind.
I want to go to the college.

57
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:36,390
You're the only one in our class
who got into the Medical University.

58
00:05:36,780 --> 00:05:38,390
You can't just give up at this point.

59
00:05:39,340 --> 00:05:40,180
Teacher Guo,

60
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:42,780
our family has two college students
out of a sudden.

61
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:45,220
My dad can't afford it.

62
00:05:46,180 --> 00:05:48,660
But, your dad shouldn't sacrifice you
because of that.

63
00:05:48,970 --> 00:05:50,980
Moreover, if you have any difficulties,

64
00:05:50,980 --> 00:05:52,740
you could apply for a student loan.

65
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:56,660
I've thought about it.

66
00:05:57,810 --> 00:05:59,040
But, attending Medical University

67
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:00,590
will take five years

68
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,270
and after graduation,

69
00:06:02,270 --> 00:06:03,630
if I want to stay
in the provincial hospital,

70
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:04,950
I'll need to go to graduate school.

71
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:06,630
It will take seven or eight years.

72
00:06:07,350 --> 00:06:09,270
But if I attend to a college,

73
00:06:09,540 --> 00:06:11,030
I can graduate in three years

74
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,340
and started earning money right away.

75
00:06:12,850 --> 00:06:14,950
Your father is so short-sighted.

76
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,830
He just wants you to earn money sooner,

77
00:06:18,270 --> 00:06:20,280
sacrificing your bright future.

78
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:23,480
Liu Yingying,

79
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,360
you can't do this.

80
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:28,680
If you do that,
you will regret it in the future.

81
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:31,280
Otherwise...

82
00:06:31,570 --> 00:06:33,210
Teacher, I've made up my mind.

83
00:06:33,570 --> 00:06:35,410
I'm going to the college.
I will not change anymore.

84
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:57,680
I couldn't bear to give up on her.

85
00:07:00,330 --> 00:07:02,480
I even thought
about talking to her father.

86
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:06,770
I visited them twice,

87
00:07:07,450 --> 00:07:08,890
but they wouldn't open the door for me.

88
00:07:11,410 --> 00:07:12,360
Then, I gave up on it.

89
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:21,720
The last time I saw her

90
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,280
was at the bus station.

91
00:07:24,290 --> 00:07:27,680
[Boarding Area]

92
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:35,450
Yingying.

93
00:07:46,450 --> 00:07:47,330
Teacher Guo.

94
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:48,530
Liu Yingying.

95
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:50,280
Teacher Guo.

96
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:52,410
Why are you here?

97
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:54,410
I'm sending my nephew off.

98
00:07:54,450 --> 00:07:55,720
He's heading for the enrollment.

99
00:07:56,090 --> 00:07:57,570
Are you going to the enrollment too?

100
00:07:58,800 --> 00:07:59,650
Teacher Guo,

101
00:07:59,650 --> 00:08:01,600
thank you for all your guidance
over the past three years.

102
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:03,480
You're in a good mood now.

103
00:08:03,970 --> 00:08:05,530
Just forget about the moment
you cried badly

104
00:08:05,530 --> 00:08:06,570
when your father asked you
to change your college option.

105
00:08:08,650 --> 00:08:09,920
I've figured it out.

106
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:11,480
Crying is useless at all.

107
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:12,920
Attending college is also a good option.

108
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:15,280
After graduation, I can still pursue a bachelor's degree
and take the postgraduate entrance examination.

109
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,920
As long as I work harder,
it will be fine.

110
00:08:17,570 --> 00:08:18,570
Once I leave here,

111
00:08:18,570 --> 00:08:20,120
my father won't be able
to control me anymore.

112
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:24,280
It's been tough for you, kid.

113
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:27,800
Remember your words, work hard.

114
00:08:27,970 --> 00:08:29,600
The bus to Jingchuan is boarding.

115
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:30,480
I get to go now.

116
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:31,360
Go ahead.

117
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:33,810
Go ahead.

118
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,930
I'm leaving, Yingying.

119
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,090
Safe journey.

120
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,400
Go back home.

121
00:09:19,290 --> 00:09:21,000
Of course, I remember Liu Yingying.

122
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:23,880
She was a notable star at our school.

123
00:09:24,970 --> 00:09:26,120
Why do you say so?

124
00:09:27,450 --> 00:09:29,090
Her college entrance exam score

125
00:09:29,090 --> 00:09:31,360
is still unbeaten at our school.

126
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:32,760
Oh, how impressive she is!

127
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:36,090
She had the score for a top-tier
university, but ended up at our college,

128
00:09:36,330 --> 00:09:37,330
she would definitely
be the most impressive one.

129
00:09:38,520 --> 00:09:41,330
She wasn't just good at studying
and ambitious,

130
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:42,760
she was also very pretty.

131
00:09:43,850 --> 00:09:44,520
Oh yeah,

132
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:47,000
she served as the student council
president for three consecutive terms.

133
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,120
She's very awesome.

134
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:48,930
Three, two, one.

135
00:09:48,930 --> 00:09:50,450
Three, two, one. Keep going!

136
00:09:50,450 --> 00:09:53,970
Keep going!

137
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:57,360
Later, she started dating a guy.

138
00:09:58,690 --> 00:09:59,810
His academic performance was average.

139
00:10:01,090 --> 00:10:02,360
But, since his parents
were government officials

140
00:10:03,210 --> 00:10:04,360
in the province,

141
00:10:05,850 --> 00:10:08,450
his family arranged for Liu Yingying

142
00:10:08,450 --> 00:10:09,600
to work at the
provincial public hospital.

143
00:10:10,810 --> 00:10:12,400
Once they graduated,

144
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:14,120
they could settle down
in the province together.

145
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:27,000
That sounds like a good match.

146
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,330
Why did they break up?

147
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:30,600
I'm not very sure

148
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,330
about the details.

149
00:10:33,170 --> 00:10:36,760
It seems like it happened
early in their last semester.

150
00:10:37,050 --> 00:10:38,330
Just a few days after school reopened,

151
00:10:38,930 --> 00:10:40,810
we heard they had broken up.

152
00:10:43,690 --> 00:10:44,520
At that time,

153
00:10:44,970 --> 00:10:48,570
there were some rumors circulating

154
00:10:49,050 --> 00:10:51,400
about Liu Yingying among her peers.

155
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,520
Some said she wasn't self-respecting,

156
00:10:55,330 --> 00:10:57,690
and others said she was involved with
more than one guy at the same time.

157
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,400
There were all kinds of stories.

158
00:11:01,210 --> 00:11:02,170
But honestly,

159
00:11:02,970 --> 00:11:04,360
even without that boy's help,

160
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:07,600
Liu Yingying could also
stay in the province

161
00:11:08,450 --> 00:11:09,600
because her academic performance

162
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:11,690
was always the best in the whole school.

163
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:14,090
Yet, the rumors

164
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,690
had quite an impact on her.

165
00:11:16,810 --> 00:11:19,600
She wasn't herself.

166
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:21,930
Once Liu Yingying graduated,

167
00:11:22,290 --> 00:11:23,520
she went back to Kulu.

168
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:25,970
I still couldn't understand

169
00:11:26,570 --> 00:11:28,520
her decision to this day.

170
00:11:31,850 --> 00:11:32,720
I couldn't understand either.

171
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:37,720
Didn't her teachers try
to reach out to her?

172
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:39,930
I did talk to her.

173
00:11:40,450 --> 00:11:41,360
But she said

174
00:11:41,810 --> 00:11:44,210
her brother had already found a job
out of the county,

175
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:46,970
and her family needed someone
to take care of them.

176
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:48,880
But, I can understand

177
00:11:49,210 --> 00:11:50,520
her reasoning.

178
00:11:51,050 --> 00:11:53,970
The demand for healthcare workers
in the rural areas was also a reality.

179
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:01,290
Here's your coffee.

180
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:09,290
Welcome, how many people do you have?

181
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,090
Are you Jiang Chao?

182
00:12:14,760 --> 00:12:15,760
I'm Chen Jianghe, from Kulu.

183
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:17,720
Officer Chen, nice to meet you.

184
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:18,520
Nice to meet you.

185
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:19,570
Please have a seat.

186
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:25,570
Here's my police ID.

187
00:12:27,970 --> 00:12:29,290
Officer Chen, would you like
to have a drink?

188
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:31,930
Anything is fine.

189
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:33,930
I'll order according to my taste then.

190
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:34,930
Sure.

191
00:12:35,690 --> 00:12:36,360
Waiter.

192
00:12:36,970 --> 00:12:37,880
Two Americanos, please.

193
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:39,600
Alright, coming right up.

194
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:41,720
Could I get some milk in one?

195
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:42,880
Sure, one with milk.

196
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:43,520
Alright.

197
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:45,720
Add some sugar
to the one with milk, please.

198
00:12:48,930 --> 00:12:50,930
You mentioned over the phone
that you had something to ask me?

199
00:12:51,570 --> 00:12:52,360
Yes, I did.

200
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:55,600
I just wanted to ask you

201
00:12:56,850 --> 00:12:58,880
about some things back
in your college years.

202
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:01,480
Was Liu Yingying your classmate?

203
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:03,210
We were at the same school,

204
00:13:03,210 --> 00:13:04,330
but not the same year.

205
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:07,600
Did you two date?

206
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:10,720
Yes, we did.

207
00:13:11,850 --> 00:13:12,930
Do you both still keep in touch?

208
00:13:13,690 --> 00:13:15,210
Since she went back to Kulu,

209
00:13:15,210 --> 00:13:16,480
we haven't been in contact.

210
00:13:17,450 --> 00:13:18,880
She never tried to reach out to you?

211
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:23,690
She did once earlier this year.

212
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:25,120
She asked to meet up.

213
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:26,930
I was surprised

214
00:13:26,930 --> 00:13:28,360
because we hadn't contacted
for so many years.

215
00:13:28,810 --> 00:13:30,120
My girlfriend happened to be with me,

216
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,090
so the three of us met up.

217
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,970
Why did you bring
your current girlfriend

218
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:39,090
to meet your ex?

219
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:40,360
What were you thinking?

220
00:13:42,810 --> 00:13:43,970
I didn't want any trouble.

221
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:48,480
You didn't want trouble?

222
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:53,170
Did Liu Yingying
ever cause you any trouble?

223
00:13:54,450 --> 00:13:55,600
Not exactly trouble.

224
00:13:55,930 --> 00:13:57,290
She just asked me for help
booking a doctor’s appointment.

225
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:58,450
What kind of appointment?

226
00:13:59,210 --> 00:14:00,360
An appointment with a specialist
at the hospital.

227
00:14:02,570 --> 00:14:04,120
She had a little girl with her
at the time

228
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:05,360
and said the child needed treatment.

229
00:14:05,970 --> 00:14:06,690
You know

230
00:14:06,690 --> 00:14:08,290
how hard it is to book
an appointment with a specialist,

231
00:14:08,330 --> 00:14:09,520
and scalpers charge a fortune.

232
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:11,720
She knew I had some connections
in the medical field,

233
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,000
so she reached out to me.

234
00:14:14,090 --> 00:14:15,050
I felt sorry for her,

235
00:14:15,050 --> 00:14:16,290
so I wanted to give her some money.

236
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:17,520
As soon as I took out the money,

237
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:18,720
she suddenly ran off.

238
00:14:19,450 --> 00:14:20,720
My girlfriend even commented

239
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:22,330
that she...

240
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:24,290
She seemed a bit abnormal.

241
00:14:25,210 --> 00:14:27,120
She has had a huge change
over the years.

242
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:28,330
I can't believe

243
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:29,930
I used to have feelings for her.

244
00:14:36,810 --> 00:14:37,760
If the two of you

245
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,760
had stayed together back then...

246
00:14:54,090 --> 00:14:55,720
How's Yingying doing these days?

247
00:14:56,330 --> 00:14:57,520
Yingying has been

248
00:14:57,520 --> 00:14:59,520
working non-stop
for two or three days straight.

249
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:10,290
Yingying, the arrangements
for the child’s funeral aren’t done yet.

250
00:15:10,290 --> 00:15:11,600
You can take your leave first.

251
00:15:13,290 --> 00:15:14,970
Work helps keep my mind off things.

252
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:19,520
Alright then.

253
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:23,330
Liang, keep an eye on things.

254
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:24,120
Alright.

255
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:26,480
Yingying,

256
00:15:27,210 --> 00:15:28,290
don't push yourself.

257
00:15:28,330 --> 00:15:29,930
If you feel like crying, just cry.

258
00:15:31,930 --> 00:15:33,330
Head nurse, I'm fine.

259
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:34,810
Thank you.

260
00:15:46,290 --> 00:15:48,400
Her child is still lying in the morgue.

261
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:49,720
But she's been working non-stop.

262
00:15:50,170 --> 00:15:52,120
She says it helps her feel better,

263
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:54,000
I think it does help.

264
00:15:54,850 --> 00:15:57,090
Since the night of the incident,
she's been at work continuously.

265
00:15:57,240 --> 00:15:58,930
Wang Liang arrived around 6:00 PM.

266
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:10,520
Manager Wang, you are here.

267
00:16:10,690 --> 00:16:12,570
Yingying is changing
the patient's dressings.

268
00:16:12,570 --> 00:16:13,930
You can wait for her inside.

269
00:16:27,290 --> 00:16:28,000
Have you eaten yet?

270
00:16:29,930 --> 00:16:30,520
No, not yet.

271
00:16:33,170 --> 00:16:34,290
You should eat something.

272
00:16:35,450 --> 00:16:36,290
I don’t have an appetite.

273
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:41,120
Yingying, you haven’t slept
in three days.

274
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:43,360
You should go rest in the break room.

275
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,330
I can handle things here.

276
00:16:45,450 --> 00:16:47,170
I’m fine, just feeling
a bit tight in the chest.

277
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:49,240
Yeah, Yingying.

278
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:50,640
Tonight we don’t have many patients.

279
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:52,090
You can go take a break.

280
00:16:52,810 --> 00:16:54,000
Sis, leave this to me.

281
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,520
Please go rest for a while.

282
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:56,810
Leave this to me.

283
00:16:58,290 --> 00:16:59,400
Thank you.

284
00:16:59,450 --> 00:17:00,810
No problem. Don't worry.

285
00:17:01,290 --> 00:17:01,570
Go rest.

286
00:17:01,570 --> 00:17:02,970
Keep an eye on the patient in bed three.

287
00:17:02,970 --> 00:17:03,480
Got it.

288
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:06,770
Manager Wang, you should
go accompany Yingying.

289
00:17:06,770 --> 00:17:07,360
Thank you.

290
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:08,120
It's nothing.

291
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:12,010
Commissioner Liu, take a look at this.

292
00:17:12,250 --> 00:17:13,960
Wang Liang entered

293
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:16,010
the hospital at 6:21 PM,

294
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:19,010
showed up at the nurse's station
at 6:29 PM,

295
00:17:19,730 --> 00:17:21,160
and went to the nurse's break room
at the end of the corridor

296
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:23,920
with Liu Yingying at 6:35 PM.

297
00:17:24,850 --> 00:17:25,880
They stayed in the break room

298
00:17:25,880 --> 00:17:27,360
until 9:40 PM.

299
00:17:27,570 --> 00:17:29,330
Then, Wang Liang left on his own

300
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:32,010
and Liu Yingying remained there.

301
00:17:32,120 --> 00:17:34,570
Her colleague checked on her
a couple of times,

302
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:36,400
confirming she stayed there
the whole time.

303
00:17:37,050 --> 00:17:40,330
She clocked out at 6:00 AM
the next morning.

304
00:17:41,090 --> 00:17:42,330
Later, we found out

305
00:17:42,490 --> 00:17:43,600
in Liu Sancheng's phone

306
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:44,770
that he called her phone.

307
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:47,090
Did Liu Yingying explain

308
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,730
why she was on the phone
with Liu Sancheng for so long

309
00:17:48,730 --> 00:17:49,600
the night of the incident?

310
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:51,880
She said after her child passed away,

311
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:54,120
she was devastated and at one
point didn’t want to live anymore.

312
00:17:54,570 --> 00:17:55,880
She was talking to Liu Sancheng,

313
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,400
sharing her feelings,

314
00:17:57,770 --> 00:18:00,050
and he consoled her.

315
00:18:00,050 --> 00:18:02,090
In the end, she promised him
she would keep living.

316
00:18:02,490 --> 00:18:03,730
She had no idea

317
00:18:04,090 --> 00:18:05,530
her father was still worried

318
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,120
and went out on his own after that.

319
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:10,090
But from the timeline,

320
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:13,330
it seems she was with Wang Liang

321
00:18:13,330 --> 00:18:14,770
while talking to Liu Sancheng
on the phone.

322
00:18:18,050 --> 00:18:19,530
Did you find any clues
at the heating station?

323
00:18:19,810 --> 00:18:21,160
All the evidence at the scene was clear.

324
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:23,530
Two years ago,
they installed a camera there,

325
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:25,160
but it broke over a year ago

326
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:26,090
and was never repaired.

327
00:18:27,530 --> 00:18:28,330
That means the heating station

328
00:18:28,330 --> 00:18:29,730
has no useful clues now.

329
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:32,680
After the incident,

330
00:18:33,570 --> 00:18:35,570
we tested the blood of the three workers

331
00:18:35,570 --> 00:18:36,680
at the heating station.

332
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:39,120
The tests showed

333
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:41,490
high levels of barbiturates

334
00:18:41,490 --> 00:18:44,680
in their blood samples,

335
00:18:45,010 --> 00:18:45,920
which explains

336
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:47,640
why they were in such a deep sleep

337
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:49,880
when we arrived.

338
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:51,680
It’s sedative.

339
00:18:53,850 --> 00:18:55,290
This is significant.

340
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:57,880
All three had barbiturates
in their blood samples?

341
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:00,250
I specially checked
on Wang Liang’s levels,

342
00:19:00,330 --> 00:19:02,120
and the results show
they all had similar amounts.

343
00:19:03,810 --> 00:19:04,960
So, does that mean

344
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:06,600
none of the three workers

345
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:09,010
could have carried the body
into the boiler?

346
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:12,330
Based on the amount of sedative
in their blood,

347
00:19:12,330 --> 00:19:13,330
it seems unlikely.

348
00:19:13,490 --> 00:19:14,770
But, there are other suspicious details.

349
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:15,920
What is that?

350
00:19:20,010 --> 00:19:20,960
After the incident,

351
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:24,400
we questioned the other two workers.

352
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:25,290
You can have a look.

353
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:27,730
They said the supper that night

354
00:19:27,730 --> 00:19:29,570
was brought by Wang Liang.

355
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:31,920
It included pork head
and half a roasted chicken.

356
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:35,680
You can see in the footage

357
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:37,920
that Wang Liang carried two plastic bags

358
00:19:37,920 --> 00:19:39,730
from the moment
he entered the hospital until he left.

359
00:19:39,850 --> 00:19:40,850
And when he and Liu Yingying

360
00:19:40,850 --> 00:19:42,920
went into the nurse’s break room,

361
00:19:43,090 --> 00:19:43,960
he placed those plastic bags

362
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:45,920
on the table at the nurse’s station.

363
00:19:47,050 --> 00:19:48,010
After they had supper,

364
00:19:48,010 --> 00:19:50,160
they threw the plastic bags
and disposable chopsticks

365
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:51,730
into the boiler.

366
00:19:52,050 --> 00:19:54,530
The beer glasses they used
were also washed.

367
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:58,010
Although we didn’t find traces of drugs

368
00:19:58,200 --> 00:19:59,810
on the beer glasses,

369
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:03,010
we can confirm

370
00:20:03,010 --> 00:20:04,770
that Wang Liang brought them the food.

371
00:20:05,850 --> 00:20:07,120
There’s one more thing

372
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:08,920
that seems suspicious to me.

373
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:09,920
Look.

374
00:20:10,570 --> 00:20:13,090
I think Wang Liang deliberately

375
00:20:13,090 --> 00:20:14,250
placed the two plastic bags

376
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:17,090
right under the surveillance camera.

377
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:20,330
That does seem deliberate.

378
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:21,640
But he ate the food himself too,

379
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:23,090
didn’t he?

380
00:20:24,250 --> 00:20:25,290
Who knows?

381
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:27,120
Maybe this is the killer's arrangement,

382
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:30,010
letting Wang Liang
to drug the workers,

383
00:20:30,050 --> 00:20:31,880
creating an opportunity
to hide the body.

384
00:20:34,530 --> 00:20:36,160
Who is the killer then?

385
00:20:37,290 --> 00:20:38,090
Liu Yingying.

386
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,360
That's unlikely.

387
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:44,050
First of all,

388
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:47,810
Liu Sancheng is her biological father.

389
00:20:49,010 --> 00:20:49,880
Also,

390
00:20:49,960 --> 00:20:51,530
how could Liu Yingying carry a man
weighing over 140 pounds

391
00:20:51,530 --> 00:20:53,530
with her small frame?

392
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:57,920
So there must be someone else
involved in this case.

393
00:21:00,010 --> 00:21:02,530
At first, I didn’t think Liu Yingying
was involved either,

394
00:21:03,090 --> 00:21:05,730
but now Wang Liang is the prime suspect.

395
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:08,250
And, Liu Yingying provided him
with an alibi.

396
00:21:08,250 --> 00:21:09,960
So, that means Liu Yingying
might be involved after all.

397
00:21:11,360 --> 00:21:11,880
Ms. Luo.

398
00:21:12,090 --> 00:21:12,920
Wang Liang is here.

399
00:21:19,330 --> 00:21:21,010
Li, have you done eating? Follow me.

400
00:21:32,050 --> 00:21:32,850
- Wang Liang.
- Ms. Luo.

401
00:21:32,920 --> 00:21:33,730
Have your seat.

402
00:21:34,880 --> 00:21:37,330
Thank you for coming.

403
00:21:38,010 --> 00:21:39,600
I know you’ve had a lot going on
at home these past few days.

404
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:44,880
Ms. Luo, why did you call me in?

405
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:46,330
Call me Officer Luo.

406
00:21:52,570 --> 00:21:53,330
Wang Liang,

407
00:21:54,530 --> 00:21:56,330
tell us exactly what you did

408
00:21:56,330 --> 00:21:58,330
on March 20th.

409
00:21:58,330 --> 00:21:59,360
Be as detailed as possible,

410
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:00,440
don’t leave anything out.

411
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:01,680
Why do I need to tell you?

412
00:22:02,090 --> 00:22:03,600
Are you suspecting me?

413
00:22:04,010 --> 00:22:05,490
It's just procedure.

414
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,920
Haven’t you been through this
twice already?

415
00:22:08,010 --> 00:22:10,090
Eight years ago, didn’t it go
like this with Chen too?

416
00:22:10,330 --> 00:22:11,200
This is for your own good.

417
00:22:17,330 --> 00:22:18,120
Just tell us.

418
00:22:19,730 --> 00:22:20,530
That day,

419
00:22:22,160 --> 00:22:24,090
I went up the mountain
to buy a stone slab.

420
00:22:25,090 --> 00:22:26,530
I wanted to make
a gravestone for Duoduo.

421
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:28,770
On the way back,

422
00:22:29,330 --> 00:22:30,600
I ran into Officer Chen,

423
00:22:31,490 --> 00:22:33,330
and he gave me a ride.

424
00:22:34,290 --> 00:22:36,330
He also took me to see Officer Sun
for a blood test,

425
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:38,330
said he wanted to help me
find my family.

426
00:22:39,120 --> 00:22:40,880
After I left Officer Sun’s place,

427
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:42,200
it was already getting late,

428
00:22:43,010 --> 00:22:44,600
and I remembered Yingying
hadn’t eaten yet,

429
00:22:46,770 --> 00:22:49,090
so I bought some cooked food
and went to the hospital to see her.

430
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:51,920
But she did not have the appetite.

431
00:22:52,250 --> 00:22:53,730
Her colleague saw us

432
00:22:53,770 --> 00:22:56,290
and suggested we rest
in the nurse’s station break room.

433
00:22:56,570 --> 00:22:57,880
I stayed there until after 9 PM.

434
00:22:57,960 --> 00:23:00,330
As she seemed to feel better, I left.

435
00:23:01,050 --> 00:23:02,400
While you were with Liu Yingying,

436
00:23:02,640 --> 00:23:05,160
did she call Liu Sancheng?

437
00:23:06,530 --> 00:23:07,330
Yes, she did.

438
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:09,400
What did they talk about?

439
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:13,490
Yingying was very upset.

440
00:23:14,050 --> 00:23:15,730
But I’m not good with words.

441
00:23:16,360 --> 00:23:18,530
I didn’t know how to comfort her.

442
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:21,160
And then you called
Liu Sancheng afterwards, didn’t you?

443
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:23,960
Yes.

444
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:26,680
What’s your relationship
with Liu Sancheng?

445
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:30,400
He was like a foster father to me.

446
00:23:33,810 --> 00:23:35,050
It’s not that simple, is it?

447
00:23:36,050 --> 00:23:36,850
Officer Luo.

448
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:48,680
Are you Duoduo's father?

449
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:53,640
What does it have to do
with my master's death?

450
00:23:54,640 --> 00:23:56,090
Just answer the questions.

451
00:23:59,490 --> 00:24:01,120
Duoduo was a mistake.

452
00:24:02,770 --> 00:24:04,530
At the time,
my sister and I were both young,

453
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:07,440
and we lost control for a moment.

454
00:24:08,010 --> 00:24:10,090
I’ve always felt deeply guilty
toward my master,

455
00:24:10,730 --> 00:24:12,120
and especially toward Yingying.

456
00:24:12,530 --> 00:24:14,290
He had only just taken me in
as his foster son,

457
00:24:14,290 --> 00:24:15,250
and I…

458
00:24:15,810 --> 00:24:17,360
How do you feel

459
00:24:18,010 --> 00:24:18,850
about Liu Sancheng’s death?

460
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:25,600
My master was very good to me.

461
00:24:26,810 --> 00:24:28,850
I was so close with him
than with my real father.

462
00:24:29,850 --> 00:24:31,250
He raised me.

463
00:24:31,570 --> 00:24:33,090
I can’t understand it.

464
00:24:33,730 --> 00:24:35,680
He never had any enemies.

465
00:24:35,680 --> 00:24:36,440
How could this happen to him?

466
00:24:37,290 --> 00:24:39,440
And, I was at the station that night,

467
00:24:40,050 --> 00:24:41,680
That person killed him

468
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:42,850
right in front of me.

469
00:24:43,090 --> 00:24:44,440
When I recall this, I...

470
00:24:46,090 --> 00:24:48,050
Officer Luo, I beg you.

471
00:24:48,530 --> 00:24:50,490
Please, I'm begging you
to find the killer.

472
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:53,050
Please, I'm begging you
to arrest the killer.

473
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:54,880
I'm begging you.

474
00:24:58,010 --> 00:25:00,250
Please, I'm begging you
to arrest the killer.

475
00:25:19,880 --> 00:25:21,440
What time did you arrive
at the hospital that day?

476
00:25:25,330 --> 00:25:26,120
6:00 PM.

477
00:25:26,530 --> 00:25:27,530
What time did you leave?

478
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:29,050
A little after 9:00 PM.

479
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:31,250
Did Liu Yingying
call Liu Sancheng first,

480
00:25:31,250 --> 00:25:32,640
or did you?

481
00:25:57,880 --> 00:25:59,050
We have rice for lunch.

482
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:00,640
Officer Luo, you are here.

483
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:01,680
I come to observe again.

484
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:03,400
One of your colleagues is inside there.

485
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:04,200
Really?

486
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:04,730
Yes.

487
00:26:07,440 --> 00:26:08,160
You are back.

488
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:18,250
Let's talk about it.

489
00:26:21,440 --> 00:26:22,120
Sure.

490
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:25,640
It's reasonable for you
to suspect Liu Yingying.

491
00:26:27,250 --> 00:26:29,290
I’m starting to think
she could be involved.

492
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:31,680
If Wang Liang drugged the workers,

493
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:34,330
the person most likely to help him
would be Liu Yingying.

494
00:26:35,640 --> 00:26:38,090
First, because of their relationship,

495
00:26:39,010 --> 00:26:41,050
and, because she works at the hospital.

496
00:26:41,330 --> 00:26:42,730
Obtaining sedatives

497
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:44,200
would be easy.

498
00:26:44,850 --> 00:26:45,730
And, look...

499
00:26:48,490 --> 00:26:50,730
Wang Liang placed the two bags of food

500
00:26:50,730 --> 00:26:52,010
in a very deliberate spot,

501
00:26:52,160 --> 00:26:53,730
right under the surveillance camera.

502
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:56,200
We all think it was intentional.

503
00:26:56,640 --> 00:26:58,120
Those two bags of food

504
00:26:58,530 --> 00:26:59,810
weren’t touched by anyone.

505
00:27:01,850 --> 00:27:03,850
If Liu Yingying gave him the drugs,

506
00:27:04,250 --> 00:27:06,090
it would’ve been easy for Wang Liang

507
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:08,050
to slip them into the food

508
00:27:08,680 --> 00:27:09,730
on his way back to the heating station.

509
00:27:12,090 --> 00:27:13,600
Even so,

510
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:15,090
we still couldn't figure out

511
00:27:16,290 --> 00:27:18,290
who actually killed Liu Sancheng.

512
00:27:19,570 --> 00:27:20,600
On the night of the incident,

513
00:27:21,290 --> 00:27:24,290
Liu Sancheng disappeared around 8:00 PM

514
00:27:25,530 --> 00:27:27,400
from an area with no surveillance

515
00:27:27,490 --> 00:27:28,850
and never appeared again.

516
00:27:30,010 --> 00:27:32,850
During that time, Wang Liang
and Liu Yingying were together

517
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:35,490
in the hospital break room.

518
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:37,360
Wang Liang left the hospital

519
00:27:37,600 --> 00:27:39,600
at around 9:40 PM,

520
00:27:39,850 --> 00:27:42,250
and arrived at the heating station
just after 10:00 PM.

521
00:27:42,770 --> 00:27:45,730
The hospital is about five kilometers
from the heating station,

522
00:27:45,880 --> 00:27:47,330
so the timing fits

523
00:27:47,530 --> 00:27:48,600
if he rode his motorcycle.

524
00:27:50,770 --> 00:27:51,770
But,

525
00:27:52,850 --> 00:27:55,640
between 8:00 PM and 10:00 PM,

526
00:27:56,770 --> 00:27:57,680
where was

527
00:27:58,360 --> 00:27:59,290
Liu Sancheng going?

528
00:28:00,330 --> 00:28:02,730
He couldn’t have just been
waiting to be killed, could he?

529
00:28:04,490 --> 00:28:05,490
I think

530
00:28:06,570 --> 00:28:08,010
there must be a third person

531
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:10,290
with Liu Yingying and Wang Liang.

532
00:28:10,850 --> 00:28:12,920
Liu Yingying and Wang Liang
handled the drugs.

533
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:15,490
And this other person killed
Liu Sancheng somewhere in between

534
00:28:15,770 --> 00:28:17,250
and then stuffed his body
into the boiler

535
00:28:17,290 --> 00:28:18,600
while everyone was asleep

536
00:28:19,050 --> 00:28:20,440
around 3:00 AM.

537
00:28:23,770 --> 00:28:24,640
What's your thought?

538
00:28:30,090 --> 00:28:31,250
That’s possible.

539
00:28:32,730 --> 00:28:35,200
Wang Liang and the two workers

540
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:38,490
ate the drugged meal

541
00:28:39,290 --> 00:28:40,570
and fell asleep

542
00:28:41,290 --> 00:28:42,600
around 11:00 PM.

543
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:46,290
But why would the killer
wait until 3:00 AM

544
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:49,050
