00:55:35,650 --> 00:55:36,400
Lend me a hand.

1090
00:55:36,560 --> 00:55:38,170
He'll be compensated
for one or two million.

1091
00:55:39,810 --> 00:55:40,610
How much?

1092
00:55:40,810 --> 00:55:41,810
One or two million.

1093
00:55:46,770 --> 00:55:48,210
Caiyun, get in the car.

1094
00:56:07,610 --> 00:56:08,330
Qiao.

1095
00:56:09,360 --> 00:56:10,040
Get down here.

1096
00:56:19,330 --> 00:56:20,560
It’s been eight or nine years.

1097
00:56:20,920 --> 00:56:22,170
Have you ever sat down and figured out

1098
00:56:22,560 --> 00:56:23,960
how much money you’ve made?

1099
00:56:24,360 --> 00:56:25,400
What do you mean by that?

1100
00:56:28,170 --> 00:56:29,810
When did you start making money?

1101
00:56:31,170 --> 00:56:31,960
Caiyun.

1102
00:56:33,360 --> 00:56:35,130
Talking about money is so low-standard.

1103
00:56:36,770 --> 00:56:37,960
Is it low-standard?

1104
00:56:38,560 --> 00:56:40,040
What can we do without money?

1105
00:56:41,400 --> 00:56:43,080
Literature is sacred.

1106
00:56:43,650 --> 00:56:46,650
Some people live for material things.

1107
00:56:47,210 --> 00:56:49,250
Some live for fame and fortune,

1108
00:56:49,480 --> 00:56:50,960
battling their way through life.

1109
00:56:50,960 --> 00:56:52,960
But we live for the spirit.

1110
00:56:53,290 --> 00:56:54,080
Caiyun.

1111
00:56:54,560 --> 00:56:57,400
Literature is our salvation.

1112
00:57:02,040 --> 00:57:02,850
Is that so?

1113
00:57:05,810 --> 00:57:07,210
I think so too.

1114
00:57:08,730 --> 00:57:10,960
Otherwise, why would

1115
00:57:11,290 --> 00:57:13,040
I have spent
the last eight or nine years

1116
00:57:13,330 --> 00:57:14,850
paying for your books to be published

1117
00:57:15,610 --> 00:57:16,400
and buying clicks?

1118
00:57:19,290 --> 00:57:22,000
But I must get
something in return, right?

1119
00:57:22,770 --> 00:57:24,960
Caiyun, my love for you,

1120
00:57:25,170 --> 00:57:26,880
isn’t that enough?

1121
00:57:33,970 --> 00:57:35,120
More than enough.

1122
00:57:37,000 --> 00:57:37,810
Qiao.

1123
00:57:38,320 --> 00:57:40,730
You know I love and pamper you the most,

1124
00:57:40,730 --> 00:57:41,240
right?

1125
00:57:41,240 --> 00:57:41,880
Yes.

1126
00:57:42,960 --> 00:57:45,120
Otherwise, I wouldn’t have given you

1127
00:57:45,520 --> 00:57:48,170
all my time and money
for the past eight or nine years.

1128
00:57:48,170 --> 00:57:48,850
Yes.

1129
00:57:49,720 --> 00:57:51,200
I’ve only ever thought about one thing.

1130
00:57:52,490 --> 00:57:53,720
I hope one day

1131
00:57:54,130 --> 00:57:55,920
you’ll take me and Zhuang

1132
00:57:56,290 --> 00:57:58,360
to the big city to make a name
for ourselves.

1133
00:57:59,450 --> 00:58:01,010
When are you going to take us?

1134
00:58:01,040 --> 00:58:02,290
That day will come.

1135
00:58:03,290 --> 00:58:04,130
Caiyun.

1136
00:58:04,720 --> 00:58:06,720
When you lean on my shoulder,

1137
00:58:07,120 --> 00:58:08,610
that’s when I love you the most.

1138
00:58:09,290 --> 00:58:11,530
I can feel my soul swaying,

1139
00:58:11,970 --> 00:58:14,840
and I know inspiration
is coming to me again.

1140
00:58:18,690 --> 00:58:20,130
I’m feeling inspired too.

1141
00:58:23,880 --> 00:58:26,730
But what does Ding Baoyuan’s release

1142
00:58:27,250 --> 00:58:28,650
have to do with us?

1143
00:58:29,730 --> 00:58:31,610
We weren’t the ones
who arrested him, right?

1144
00:58:31,960 --> 00:58:34,650
Whoever arrested him,
let him go after them.

1145
00:58:34,730 --> 00:58:36,570
So why do we have to leave?

1146
00:58:36,920 --> 00:58:38,000
We’re not leaving.

1147
00:58:39,130 --> 00:58:39,920
Not leaving?

1148
00:58:41,040 --> 00:58:42,520
But if he finds out we tricked him,

1149
00:58:43,170 --> 00:58:44,400
if he knows about our relationship,

1150
00:58:44,440 --> 00:58:45,810
do you think he’ll let me off?

1151
00:58:46,770 --> 00:58:48,480
How could he know?

1152
00:58:49,090 --> 00:58:49,770
Grab this.

1153
00:58:50,320 --> 00:58:51,880
He’s been in prison for eight years.

1154
00:58:52,130 --> 00:58:53,650
I visited him every month.

1155
00:58:54,130 --> 00:58:54,880
Moreover,

1156
00:58:55,320 --> 00:58:57,520
after eight years in prison,
he’s probably lost his mind.

1157
00:58:57,650 --> 00:58:59,360
It’ll be a miracle if he can
remember how to eat and drink.

1158
00:58:59,960 --> 00:59:01,400
We’ll figure out a way

1159
00:59:01,440 --> 00:59:02,960
to get that million or two
in compensation.

1160
00:59:03,130 --> 00:59:04,130
We can't leave.

1161
00:59:04,520 --> 00:59:05,360
Not leaving?

1162
00:59:05,480 --> 00:59:07,360
But, there will be four of us...

1163
00:59:08,440 --> 00:59:09,960
Are you silly?

1164
00:59:10,480 --> 00:59:11,770
Writing makes you lose your senses.

1165
00:59:13,130 --> 00:59:15,170
I'll stay here with Zhuang.

1166
00:59:15,250 --> 00:59:16,840
You should go back home for now.

1167
00:59:17,090 --> 00:59:18,320
I don’t have a home anymore.

1168
00:59:18,320 --> 00:59:19,730
My old house was demolished.

1169
00:59:19,730 --> 00:59:20,730
Where can I go?

1170
00:59:22,690 --> 00:59:24,920
You can stay
at your sister’s house for now.

1171
00:59:25,320 --> 00:59:27,960
We’ll work out

1172
00:59:28,130 --> 00:59:30,320
how to get
that compensation money later.

1173
00:59:32,320 --> 00:59:33,210
You go and wait for me.

1174
00:59:33,960 --> 00:59:36,000
We can’t meet each other
for a while, understand?

1175
00:59:36,130 --> 00:59:36,570
Leave now.

1176
00:59:36,570 --> 00:59:36,920
Okay.

1177
00:59:37,610 --> 00:59:38,290
Come on.

1178
00:59:40,360 --> 00:59:41,960
Let me say something to the child.

1179
00:59:52,170 --> 00:59:52,810
Father.

1180
00:59:52,960 --> 00:59:53,730
Kid,

1181
00:59:55,650 --> 00:59:56,520
in a few days,

1182
00:59:56,730 --> 00:59:58,730
the uncle from prison

1183
00:59:58,920 --> 01:00:00,170
will be staying at our home.

1184
01:00:00,690 --> 01:00:03,570
When he comes, you’re going
to call him ‘Father',

1185
01:00:03,960 --> 01:00:04,810
okay?

1186
01:00:05,290 --> 01:00:05,880
No.

1187
01:00:06,960 --> 01:00:07,770
Be good.

1188
01:00:08,650 --> 01:00:09,520
Don't forget, okay?

1189
01:00:16,160 --> 01:00:21,360
♪Who's looking for gold?♪

1190
01:00:23,880 --> 01:00:29,230
♪Who stole the sheep?♪

1191
01:00:31,570 --> 01:00:38,420
♪The sand slips into my nerves♪

1192
01:00:39,320 --> 01:00:44,630
♪The world's changes are bothering me♪

1193
01:01:18,030 --> 01:01:23,690
♪Whose throat has been ripped out
by the wind?♪

1194
01:01:25,770 --> 01:01:31,570
♪Quicksand, cinders,
who will be cremated?♪

1195
01:01:33,490 --> 01:01:39,790
♪Whose throat has the wind
ripped out again?♪

1196
01:01:41,180 --> 01:01:48,710
♪Quicksand, tell me all the answers♪
